The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | IIT Kanpur student drinks poison
                                                                                                               IIT Kanpur student drinks poison
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Lucknow, Aug. 10: A fourth-year mechanical engineering student attempted suicide by consuming poison at IIT Kanpur during golden jubilee celebrations last evening.         
	Dhirendra Kumar consumed a liquid mosquito repellent in his hostel room when the 50th foundation day programme was on.         
	Kumar was rushed to a hospital, and then taken to a private nursing home near the campus.         
	He was kept in the ICU and his condition was stated to be stable, Ravi Shukla, spokesperson for the IIT, said.         
	We were taken unawares by the students sudden move to end his life, IIT Kanpur registrar Sanjeev Kashalkar said.         
	Superintendent of police (crime) .P. Singh said a case would be registered only after a thorough investigation.         
	Dr Sanjay Dhande, the director of IIT Kanpur, said the incident had left the institute stunned but added the suicide bid had nothing to do with the institute.         
	He had a personal problem which I dont want to discuss, Dhande said.         
	The IIT Kanpur administration has set up a four-member inquiry committee.         
	A report will be submitted to the director in three days.                                                                                                                                                                           
